Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim, then cut the @butternut squash{1} in half lengthways. Scoop out the seeds and cut into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop on a large #baking tray{}. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Drizzle the butternut with @oil{}, add the @ground coriander{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to evenly coat.

Pop the baking tray onto the top shelf of your oven and roast the butternut until soft and golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. ~{10%minutes} into the cooking time, add the aubergine to the tray with the squash and toss everything together before returning to the oven. Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Zest then halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Pour the @water for the bulgur{240%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120} and @vegetable stock powder{1}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the red onion. Stir-fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the lentils. Lower the heat to medium and warm through for ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove the frying pan from the heat and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks discarded) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop. Keep the herbs separate. Crumble the @feta cheese{100} into a #mixing bowl{} with half the mint and a glug of @olive oil{}. Once the bulgur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and add it to the pan with the lentils. Mix in the parsley and remaining mint along with a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

When the butternut and aubergine chunks are cooked, spoon on the @red pepper and chilli jelly{2}. Carefully toss the roasted veg in the jelly so it gets an even coating. Serve the bulgur lentil mixture in deep #bowls{} with some butternut and aubergine on top, a sprinkling of minty feta and any remaining lemon zest. Enjoy!